description: Jack Ryder is in a mental health facility by his own admission.  He's worried about missing time.  He's plagued by dreams.  The Creeper is waiting to get out of Jack.
name: Screaming to Get Out

description: With Batman back in town, the two heroes tapped some of Desmond's associates lines looking for something to tie him to the 21 dead gangsters. They got the needed confessions and attacked. Batman took care of Lady Vic and Stallion while Nightwing went after Blockbuster. Battling it out under his house, Desmond knocked out a support beam, bringing the structure down on himself. Batman and Nightwing left him for dead.
name: Warriors Two
The Rabbit Rampant

description: Superboy, Robin and Impulse lend several helping hands as the Legion takes on C.O.M.P.U.T.O.
name: When the Reign Comes

description:
General Notes

Like the issue before, this issue takes its title from an entity of Voudun mythology, in this case Erzulie Freda. As the mysteries of the series start to become clearer, the name Erzulie is mentioned in connection with the character herself although she usually just goes by Freda and while Voodoo makes forays into studying her namesake it does not seem she makes the connection between the names in the books she reads and the names of the strange individuals she has met since arriving in New Orleans yet.
name: Erzulie

description:
Synopsis

Doctor Strange is confronted by Loki, god of mischief, an old foe. After a brief discussion, Lokis suddenly becomes very scared, and vanishes in an explosion, leaving Doctor Strange to himself, confused. He is then shown with Ashema, who seemingly kills him.

At the Baxter Building, Franklin Richards confronts a family that does not know him. He reaches his mother, who recognizes him despite the memory losses. Spider-Man is then shown heading to confront the Hulk, who is in Central Park.

While wandering around the park, Hulk is confronted by Doc Samson and the Thunderbolts, who unsuccessfully attempt to calm him. Thor later joins the battle.

Back at the Place of No Rain, Franklin Richards is angrily confronting Ashema for taking him away from his parents. He gets angry at her and blasts her, fleeing afterwards. Back at the Baxter Building, the Fantastic Four are facing the problem of two fireballs.

It, lastly, shows two Hulks appearing in Central Park, as one was transported across universes. All combatants stand in astonishment at this revelation.
name: Second Coming

description: Sitting around in a beat up house Luse passes out and has another talk with Parintachin. Then Luse makes his final run at Jace.
name: Five: With Friends Like These...

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

description: Heroes must play ball with the villains! Not literally PLAY BALL, actually.
name: Third Dimension

description:
Nearly all the heroes currently in the pocket universe have gathered in preparation to attempt the trip home. Mr. Fantastic, Tony Stark, Bruce Banner and Dr. Doom make the final checks on the ark, while Captain America bids good-bye to his partner Bucky. Ashema, the Celestial in human form, reiterates that once the heroes return, the pocket universe will be obliterated and Franklin Richards will accompany her to the realm of the Celestials. As one, the heroes refuse to comply, and Ashema threatens the destruction of both universes. However, she looks into Franklin's pleading eyes, and relents, on the condition that all must leave the pocket universe and return to their native universe together.

Meanwhile, on another plane, Dr. Strange adds his magic to aid the return.

The heroes board Doom's ark and begin their journey by first shifting into the Microverse, then traversing the Negative Zone. Then, without warning, Dr. Doom, envious of the power within Franklin, abducts the boy, and leaves the ark for the void of the Negative Zone. However, Mr. Fantastic retrieves Franklin by stretching to take him from Doom's grasp, while Thor tackles the despot. Thor and Doom hurtle away from the ship while Iron Man pilots it through the barrier between the worlds. As they cross, those aboard the ark recall memories the didn't know they had lost.

Then the ark shatters, and its passengers are hurled in various directions. The Hulk and Banner merge, while the Fantastic Four and Franklin find themselves in parts unknown, but on Earth. Sue Richards witnesses a vision of Ashema, who agrees to allow Franklin to remain, and to leave the pocket universe intact.

In the far reaches of space, Ashema, in her true Celestial form, lies dreaming, maintaining the pocket universe, which now rests in the hand of Eternity.
name: Fourth & Goal

description:
After the high-octane events of the previous arc, Tommy Monaghan finally gets a bit of rest from the super-powered and supernatural--which leaves room for his personal life to go a little crazy when he and Tiegel officially start a relationship!

Tommy's attempt to relax and have a happy day leaves him landing literally in the middle of a deal. He tries to calm the situation but it goes badly and bullets fly and the wrong, wrong people die.The effects of this issue will last through the rest of the series.
name: Kiss Me

volume.name: Corto Maltese: Ballad of the Salt Sea
Corto Maltese: Ballad of the Salt Sea

description:
Overview
The world lies beneath the heel of Chaos. But it is the spawn of Chaos, Elric of Melnibonè, who is destined to bring order to the planet, to strike the balance between Chaos and Law. P. Craig Russell's outstanding adaptation of Michael Moorcock's classic novel continues! Copublished with Topps.
name: The Lords of Law and the Horn of Fate

description:
Overview
Two men, clad in sorcerous garb and armed with weapons forged by gods. This is what it comes down to, this grand battle between Law and Chaos, this struggle for control of the earth. P. Craig Russell takes you on the home stretch of this most fantastic of epics, the comics adaptation of Michael Moorcock's greatest novel. Copublished with Topps.
name: The Comedy is Over

description: Beginning a 3-issue miniseries delving into the past and future of Destiny of the Endless, with painted covers and framing sequences by Kent Williams. In the year 2009, a small town holds out against a devastating pandemic, its remaining inhabitants desperately hoping to survive the next outbreak of plague. Then a mysterious stranger arrives from nowhere, selling a page that he claims is not only taken from the Book of Destiny, but also foretells the four great plagues of humankind, including where the current one will strike next. To convince them of its worth, he offers to read from the page, revealing Destiny's role--as well as his own--in the previous three plagues, starting with the epidemic that struck the Byzantine empire.
name: Byzantium

volume.name: Destiny: A Chronicle of Deaths Foretold

description: Trapped in another dimension, the Golden Age Flash must team up with the Modern Age Green Lantern, and the Golden Age Green Lantern must team up with the Modern Age Flash, in order to avert an alien invasion of Earth. Interestingly, the younger heroes seem to have switched powers.

In a world where Superman rocketed to Earth in 1938, Clark Kent has hardly aged a day by 1996, while his beloved Lois Lane has watched herself grow older with each passing year, with the gulf between immortal man and mortal woman ever widening. But when Lois gets the chance to obtain her heart's desire, she finds herself transformed by the power of ancient gods into the Man of Steel's perfect mate--a Wonder Woman whose life and love will endure as long as Superman's.
name: The Dream

description: Continuing the miniseries delving into the past and future of Destiny of the Endless. Welcomes warily into a community of holdouts from a modern-day plague, the mysterious John Ryder continues to tell his tale based on a prophetic page torn from the Book of Destiny. His second story, beautifully illustrated by Scott Hampton, captures a moment in time just before the Black Death overtook Europe in the 1300s, as seen through the eyes of a young princess for whom marriage is literally a matter of life and death.
name: Black Death

volume.name: Destiny: A Chronicle of Deaths Foretold

description: The search for Lana Lang takes Lois and Clark to the heart of the Third Reich, where their true foes reveal themselves...and where each discovers his/her true destiny. For one, triumph; for another, tragedy; for the third...truth!
name: The Hunt

description: The enigmatic John Ryder reads the third and final tale from his prophetic book, which contains a page stolen from Destiny's own ancient tome of knowledge. This final story recounts the fate of a young woman living in a small English village in the 17th century, during the time of the Great Plague. Yet past and present intersect in unexpected ways as ancient predictions are fulfilled and Ryder finds himself at a crossroads, forced to choose between love...and Destiny.
name: Eyam

volume.name: Destiny: A Chronicle of Deaths Foretold

description: Lois Lane becomes Wonder Woman! The sacrifice of the goddess Athena endows Lois with the power she's always wanted. But first, Lois must defeat the champion of Nazi Germany--Princess Diana! Meanwhile, Lana Lang pursues Superman, who has fallen prey to the enchantress Circe. All three will win their hearts' desires, but they should have been more careful about what they wished for.
name: The Gift

description: The mythic conclusion to the romance of the century! Superman and Lois Lane overcome obstacles of legendary proportions to thwart the gods at their own game. And in the end, their fated love literally conquers all.
name: The Price

description: Still making his way across America, Tim meets someone who's even more angry and desperate than he is. Her name is Judith, a runaway en route to join her sister as a go-go dancer, and who's less than thrilled to have a geeky kid like Tim tagging along. But they're both in for a rude surprise and a deadly confrontation when they arrive at the X-rated club and find a man who looks strangely like a Minotaur. Apparently, he's been travelling centuries to meet them.
name: Horn

description:
Overview

 The Man of Steel was beginning to grow up. The Superman who debuted in Action Comics 1 in June, 1938 was one tough monkey, a hero who thought nothing of smashing through the governor's bedroom door in the middle of the night in order to get what he wanted. Who would hang a bad guy by the heels high over the city to scare the needed information out of him. Who smacked around an abusive husband as a way of giving the man a taste of his own medicine. Who fought (mainly) guys in suits out to screw over the little guy. Tough... but, in his own way, mellowing. Which isn't to say that the Superman of those second and third years in Action was going soft. He was still a hero of the people, a post-Depression, pre-War populist who battled exploiters of child labor, insurance fraud targeted at the elderly, and crooked doctors who claimed to be able to cure polio, to name but a few... Whatever wrong faced the honest citizens of the world, whichever bully threatened Joe and Jane Average was confronted head-on by the one guy who couldn't be hurt, wouldn't be intimidated. The hero determined to outbully the worst bully. Superman.
name: Volume 2

deck: Despero fights free of L-Ron's control, and it's up to Supergirl to stop him.
description: Despero reasserts control from L-Ron over his body; Supergirl undergoes another change.
name: Teetering On Oblivion
The Spook

description: The team-up you never thought you'd see: the Kid and...Natasha Irons? Perhaps romance is in the air, but will Nat's uncle--John Irons, aka Steel--vent his problems with their possible relationship?
name: Bori

description: Bart must recover from his heart-wrenching betrayal quickly, or the future may just go up in smoke! More consequences of the Simms family's activities in the forties! And something BIG may be coming to Earth, and it ain't Orson Welles!
name: Trials With Tribulations!

description: The Dark Dozen launches its master plan to bring Masterlord Akuma onto the prime material plane!

volume.name: Solar, Man Of The Atom: Hell On Earth

description: The true alien origins of the X-O armor revealed! But will the truth save Donovan, or will the dark secrets of this ultimate weapon consume him?
name: The Chosen

description:
Overview
Abducted by extraterrestrials; his brain transplanted. Ron Lithgow needs help if he is to understand his new body and his new life. The NSA and the CIA lend a hand . . . in exchange for exclusive rights to study his alien form. Yet the agencies exhibit little concern for the man trapped inside -- except for one researcher, the beautiful Maureen Vonnegut. Ron Lithgow, aka Concrete, is headed for a fall. Paul Chadwick retells Concrete's origin with new revelations and amazing new details. Experience it all again for the first time!

OverviewSomewhere in the ravaged jungles of 24th Century Africa, Tarzan and his son Korak must face invading hordes of Vagas from the Earth's moon. But even as the jungle lord's piercing cry strikes fear into the hearts of the Vagas, it is drowned out by the roar of rockets bringing fresh troops to Earth!
name: Tarzan vs. The Moon Men (Part 2 of 4)

description: Inazuma is tormented by dreams as she lies helpless and in the hands of Jei, the demonic spearman. Usagi finally gets possession of the sword of the gods but is unaware of its importance. Meanwhile, warriors of the Imperial faction are right behind him. One member of the Conspiracy of Eight plan the assassination of Lord Noriyuki as he travels to Edo for the installation of the new shogun.
name: Grasscutter, Chapter 3: Inazuma

description: Dick Grayson shows his disaprovel to Batman for his crime fighting techniques and his attitude towards the untrained Batgirl. After watching Babs and Dick play tennis, Bruce figures out that Barbara is actually Batgirl and decides to train her, much to the anger of Grayson.
name: Book One: Lost Years

volume.name: The Batman Adventures: The Lost Years

description: "Spook" part 1! A blizzard is approaching as a handful of the most wealthy and influential individuals on Earth gather at an isolated mountain lodge to meet with Bruce Wayne. But when the lights go out and the servants all disappear, people begin to die, one by one.
name: Spook: One of Three

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Moreland McShane learns that Selina Kyle is Catwoman, and Catwoman makes a shocking discovery of her own.
name: Nightcrossed

description: The Challengers and Batman are cast adrift in time by Sands' old friend Paul Hemmings.

Mirror Master ambushes Wally at Linda Park's home.  He's trapped her in a mirror dimension and if the Flash doesn't do something about it in the next fifteen minutes, she'll be stuck there forever.

Unfortunately for Wally, Mirror Master's illusions are enough to fool him into running through a prism at the speed of light.  This splits the Flash into seven different colored versions.  By the time the Flash can escape Mirror Master's trap, McCulloch has already robbed the Keystone National Bank.

Mirror Master continues to hold off the Flash with illusions and mirror duplicates but the Flash manages to break McCulloch's gun...without which Linda will be trapped forever.  Mirror Master sends the Flash to Singapore to pick up replacement parts and then he frees Linda with one minute to spare...or so he says.  Wally is given the choice to catch the crook or make sure his girlfriend is alright.

Flash chooses to check on Linda but after finding her to be okay, he runs back and catches the Mirror Master.  McCulloch laughs, knowing he can escape his cell no problem...until the Flash turns out the lights.
name: Through the looking Glass!

description: The conclusion to this special 2-issue miniseries reuniting Tim Hunter with John Constantine, his original mentor in magic. When Tim accompanies John on a harrowing journey into the darkest corners of the older man's personal hell, a battle for Constantine's soul ensues--and survival will require that Tim prove himself to be at least his mentor's equal.
name: Book Two: Descent

description:
It's a holiday-themed HITMAN Christmas special! Everything seems quiet on Christmas Eve, but all heck breaks loose when a radioactive Santa goes on a rampage through the street of Gotham!

Tommy and Natt have no money for Christmas presents this year.

That is until they get a contract to take out a crazed super-villain dressed as Santa Claus.

Notes:

  • Ranked #93 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: The Santa Contract

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: Manchester Junior High has a new school counselor and he brings up the fact that Bart has no record of guardianship papers, birth certificate and no record of his father's death. But Max contacts his friend to make some. Bart makes a plan to capture White Lightning.
name: Time out

description:
Renouncing heaven and his own immortality for love, guardian angel Zauriel has decided to approach the woman he risked everything for. Zauriel goes to San Francisco, and visits sales assistant Shannon Coyne, the woman he had been tasked with protecting. Laying his heart on the line, Zaureil professes his love, leaving Shannon shocked.
 
Meanwhile, Asmodel, Zauriel’s arch-enemy and a fallen angel of the bull host, plans his revenge for being defeated by Zauriel and the Justice League. Asmodel had approached Neron, one of the most powerful demons of hell, for an alliance. Now, however, with Zauriel’s presence, Neron worries about interference from the guardian angel and his allies in the Justice League. Neron sends Etrigan the Demon after Zauriel.
 
At Shannon’s apartment, Etrigan attacks the couple. Zauriel draws Etrigan and the fight away from Shannon, and the two fight in the streets of San Francisco. Eventually, Zauriel convinces Etrigan to side with him; if Neron’s plans were wrecked, then Etrigan would rise in ranks amongst the lords of hell. Etrigan appreciates Zauriel’s thinking, and leaves.
 
Meanwhile, at the Justice League Watchtower on the Moon, Martian Manhunter is on monitor duty when a seemingly young child enters the Watchtower. The child reveals himself to be Asmodel, wearing a “flesh-suit.” Asmodel pummels Martian Manhunter in revenge for the League defeating his prior plans. He leaves Martian Manhunter for dead on the Moon’s surface, on the hunt for Zauriel.
name: Someone to Watch Over Me

description: Billy gets kidnapped; Gangbuster helps rescue him.
name: With Friends Like These..

description:
The conclusion of our heroes' New Orleans trip: with Cassidy in big trouble and Jesse trapped in a voodoo-inspired trance, it's up to Tulip to hold off a deadly assault by Les Enfants Du Sang. Plus, Jesse gets another piece of the puzzle about Genesis; Xavier gives Tulip a dire warning about Cassidy; and Arseface sets off on the path to superstardom.

Les Enfents du Sang make their play to get Cassidy and Tulip, and meet a series of unfortunate ends; Xavier warns Tulip that Cassidy is not to be trusted; Arseface sets out on a whole new life.
name: Price of Night

description: Still reeling from the death of young El, Robin returns to Paris in the hopes of finding the answers to his own questions. Has he chosen the right path? He seeks the master of the iron hand for answers. King Snake is lured into the picture when one of his ship's crew are attacked and killed swiftly.
name: Robin is History!

description: The New York police thought they were prepared for the coin collecting convention, but the lure of Nazi gold brought in a criminal element they couldn't have anticipated!
name: The Cannon Act II of IV

description: Confronting a seemingly insane God, the Spectre learns secrets about Jim Corrigan’s father that may finally let him rest.
name: The Face of God

description:
In a self-contained story, Ice Maiden, Crimson Fox, Amazing Man II, Blue Devil and Firestorm form the new Justice League Europe! Too bad they're in the way of the Mist's plans. So, the villainess and mother of Jack's child has a simple, but elegant solution to the problem: kill them.

Mist tackles the new Justice League Europe and kills three of its members.

Death of Amazing Man II, Blue Devil, and Crimson Fox,
name: ... La Fraternite de Justice et Liberte!

description: Bibbo is Superman's friend--at least, that's what he tells his disbelieving pals in the Ace O' Clubs! But when Bibbo stumbles onto a huge sting operation gone awry, will his favorite hero be there to help, or must Bibbo fight alone?
name: Maximum Effort!

description:
In this self-contained issue, journalist Spider Jerusalem watches TV, alternating between (1.) violent reactions to what's considered entertainment in his City, and (2.) an apathetic state bordering on decomposition.

Spider decides to spend the whole day watching television, claiming it will help him better understand the residents of the City. After several hours of aimless channel surfing and buying products he sees in commercials, Spider discovers the wonder of call-in shows. However, when the chaos he is causing starts making the news, Spider is forced to realize the horrible truth: he has become television.
name: What Spider Watches on TV

description: Hippolyta makes her debut as the replacement Wonder Woman as the turn-of-the-century supercomputer, Egg Fu, is revealed to be more than a mere carnival attraction! It's a product of New Genesis technology, with a deadly purpose that threatens the lives of Artemis and Donna Troy!
name: Harvest of Souls
The Twenty-Four Carat Moon; Time Bandits

description: Sam and Twitch are called to the home of their client, Mrs. Byrd, whose husband has been murdered. As they drive away, puzzling over the scene of the crime, Cog mysteriously appears in the back seat of the '55 Chevy and asks them to help Spawn. Meanwhile, back in the alley, Spawn's murderer bags up the necroplasm as evidence of his death and takes it to his boss, the Freak. When the bums hear of their protector's demise, the battle for the alley begins.
name: Intersection

description:
Steve Rogers finds himself on the streets of Tokyo with no memory of where he has been for the last year. Before he can get his bearings, Captain America is called into action to stop a group of terrorists who are protesting the Americanization of Japanese culture.

Captain America finds himself back on Earth in the middle of Japan. He's confused by the amount of excessive veneration he receives but puts it aside to save innocent lives from a bombing plot.
name: The Return of Steve Rogers

description: The Thunderbolts take over! The H4H Team, Kro's rebel forces, the Eternals Thena, and Seris battle Ghaur's forces!
name: The Thunderbolts Take Over!

description: Ka-Zar battlles Thanos.
name: Urban Jungle (Chapter Two): It's a Jungle Out There
Need to Know

description:
Cypher readies Illyana Rasputin for her brother Mikhail to transport the dormant Legacy virus cells out of her body, but the process goes awry, and they have to rush her to the ICU.   The younger Rahne Sinclair breaks off from the rest.    Sam wakes in a cell with the rest of the older former New Mutants. He places Douglock in contact with the containment field, shocking him awake, and they rouse the others.

Despite his attempt to cure his sister, Mikhail will not deviate from his own agenda.  He tells the younger New Mutants that Illyana is free of the virus.  However, Doug Ramsey is suspicious and investigates.   He soon learn she was originally healthy and Mikhail actually infected her, under the assumption that her mystical self would develop an immunity whereas her younger self (who died from the virus) could not.

If Illyana could become immune, Mikhail could possibly cure his own infection. Inadvertently, Doug also learns of his own death.

Young Rahne sneaks off to free the older mutants, but Mikhail stops her. They free themselves anyway, and attack him.  Illyana and the New Mutants confront Mikhail with the truth, and he teleports away.

Karma wipes out the young New Mutants' memories of their trip to their future as they go back to the past via Illyana’s portal. The present-day New Mutants reminisce and visit Illyana's grave.
name: Letting Go

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Quicksilver continues to duel with Arkon of Polemachus, when Crystal of the Inhumans bursts back on the scene! After being transported to one of Franklin Richards’ dimensions, Crystal returns to Earth alongside the Fantastic Four and Avengers. Pietro reunites with the woman he loves.

Crystal returns from the Franklin Richards universe along with the Avengers and the Fantastic Four.
name: KIller Instinct

description: After defeating Buel, Spider-Man and Doctor Strange must travel through odd and violent realities in order to find the Sphere of Sara-Kath.
name: The Spirit is Willing: The Flesh...

description: A Telepathy War tie-in! The Jem'Hadar attack on Deep Space Nine rages on as Worf takes the Defiant into battle against the orders of Captain Sisko! Meanwhile on DS9 itself, raiding parties threaten the station's crew and the runaway fugitive cadets of Omega Sqad! Can the combined forces of DS9 and the U.S.S. Enterprise-E turn the tide of battle?
name: Telepathy War, Part 4: Day of Honor

description:
In this issue the crew mends the ship after the attack by the Chakuum.  Do to the Battles the Federation is short good officers and Number One is offered the command of the U.S.S. Nelson.  Meanwhile Captain Pike is sent on a secret mission and none other than Admiral Robert April arrives on the ship as an adviser to Number One.
 
Mia Colt and Jose Tyler find an object known as a Keepsake on the planet Algol.  Defying Federation protocol she takes in to the ship to investigate it's structure.  This ends with the object zapping her and having her wake up in a future time.
name: Futures (Part One)

description: The cosmic beings Q and Trelane tweak reality so Captain Picard and Captain Kirk now command each other's ships.
name: An Infinite Jest

description: Desperately needing an element that can recharge the ship's systems, the crew beams down to a world with floating cities. There, Tom gets separated from the crew and has to face an illegal mining operation -- alone!
name: Telepathy War, Part 5; Cloud Walkers

description: The Thunderbolts are revealed to the world as the Masters of Evil!
name: Heroes' Reward

description: What if the Impossible Man obtained the Infinity Gauntlet?
name: Finders Keepers
Messiah Complex Part One: The Ride

description:
Finding himself in the "Days of Future Past" alternate future, Access comes under attack by Sentinels, but is rescued by the Legion of Super-Heroes. Soon, they are found by Logan, who leads them to meet the rest of what's left of the X-Men. Brainiac 5 then devises for the X-Men a field nullifier which counteracts the inhibitor collars they are forced to wear. The Legion offers their aid in defeating the Sentinels, but the X-Men decline, and Access sends the Legionnaires back to their own timeline. Before Ferro can go through the portal, however, a Sentinel attacks. Ferro and Colossus topple it, but more arrive. Magneto shoves Ferro and Access through the portal as the Sentinels destroy the nullifier and cripple Magneto. Logan escapes, inspired to formulate a plan to beat the robots.

Access now bounces back and forth between the two universes and into pasts and futures, until he is yanked into Central Park by Morty, the bum from whom Axel Asher received his Access powers. Access thought Morty had died, but as they converse, he realizes Morty is his future self. With two Accesses in close proximity a wide portal opens. Morty teleports away, but not quickly enough to prevent the arrival of Darkseid and his hordes from Apokolips. Coveting Access' universe-crossing abilities, Darkseid makes him an offer to join him, but just then the Avengers (from early in their career) intervene. A battle ensues, and although Access is held in the grip of Devilance, he manages to open a portal and pull the JLA through. Feeling the tide turn, Darkseid orders Amazing Grace to take control of the minds of the male heroes, forcing them to face off amongst themselves, while he and his minions escape.
name: Let's Do the Time Warp Again!

description:
Chuck is very surprised to see Rachael on the arm of the senator and then angry. 
 
Walsh turns up at the apartment disguised as a pizza delivery man. He subtly hints he can get Katchoo out of there. Kat refuses and says she has to see this through and has no plan as yet.                                           
                                             
At the function Francie catches Katchoo's eye and is stunned to see her friend in makeup and a dress. Kat drags her into a bathroom and comes out a few minutes later. Francine emerges blushing with a dreamy look on her face. Katchoo meets a reporter at the function and gives him the scoop on the entire  scam which is printed in a major paper the next morning. 
 
Tambi delivers the paper to Darcy who is utterly devastated at her undoing. Tambi dispassionatly murders her with a shot to the face. then, dressing the scene, she puts the gun in Darcy's hand and takes a Polaroid. 
 
David attends his sisters grave and is reunited with Katchoo and Francine.
name: The Danger of the Night

description:
Kevin Matchstick and Joe Phat drive to Montreal to search for the mystery behind the recent congregation of the forces of darkness in that city.  Kirby has left to pursue his own Labors.
 
Joe and Kevin trail a basilisk but lose him.  Then they fight a group of gargoyles, and are once again rejoiced by Kirby.   Kirby is glad to join up with them for now, but is not sure if he wants to stay as an independent warrior.  They also meet Kim Song, the Monkey King, another avatar, who tells them that several other avatars have arrived in the city.  Kirby shows them the cross on Mount Royal, which the heroes all recognize as the site of evil from their earlier vision.
 
It  turns out that the Pale Incanter has been siphoning off part Kevin's power whenever he uses it.  He is then using that power to slowly bring his golem to life.
name: Come What Come May

description:
While Matt recovers from his wounds, Karen blows off steam, (and spite), with a shopping spree on Matt’s credit card. Daredevil meets up with Black Widow to discuss the kiss they shared. Is DD’s love with Karen in jeopardy? Has he at long last been caught in Widow’s web?

Matt fears getting too close to Natasha, and Foggy's sister wanders off with an ominous stranger.
name: Fallout

description: Warrant is back with a vengeance! The man once suspected of orchestrating the deaths of Eric and Woody's fathers, has become a mentor to Quantum, leaving Woody in the dust. But never fear, Woody partners up with someone who's got a ton more sense then Quantum.
name: KYAG

description: It's nearly two decades in the future--and the world is a very different place. North America is controlled by the Sentinels and their National Security Force led by...Helmut Zemo! Magneto and Jubilee have found the only man alive with the abilities to undertake the mission that could stop the wave of natural cataclysms assaulting the planet--but Wolverine has no idea who they are!
name: Uneasy Alliances

description:
A fun series that focuses primarily on the interplay of the personalities of the League members. After individually defeating a different alien threat, known collectively as the Appellax, Martian Manhunter, Green Lantern (Hal Jordan), Flash (Barry Allen), Black Canary (Dinah Lance), and Aquaman each consider the potentials of forming and working as a team. While meeting to confront the final Appellax, Black Canary teaches Barry some techniques from the Golden Age Flash, while Green Lantern, Martian Manhunter, and Aquaman realize the power of their combined strength and ability to compensate for each other's weakness. Meanwhile Locus, the militarized group connected to the Appellax, also realizes the ramifications of facing a unified team of heroes.

A new generation of heroes meet for the first time, planting the seeds of what would become the greatest super hero team in history.
name: Justice League of America: Year One

description: The government enlists the Heroes to help capture the fear-causing Scarecrow. It goes badly.
name: Take No Prisoners to the Twilight of the Gods!
Finder

description:
Doctor Polaris enters the city and causes trouble for Aquaman. Aquaman tries to probe him telepathically, but Dolphin accidentally interferes. Then, Maxima arrives.

Dr. Polaris arrives in Poseidonis, and he attacks Aquaman using his powers on Aquaman's hook flinging him around the dome. However Garth and Dolphin arrive to help but Tempest is almost killed when the hook is turned on him until Polaris releases him deeming it to easy. The firm in charge of Poseidonis's tourist industry are going over the figures, when a woman bursts in demanding their handling her trip their to make Aquaman her king, while Aquaman give sup the harpoon for an artificial hand until he learns what cause the trip.

Garth and Dolphin then notice increased pointing and whispering around the city, demanding to know what happened they learn the rumor that Aquaman tried to kill Garth for his relationship with Dolphin. Dr. Polaris then confronts Aquaman attacking him once again much to Vulko's joy as Koryak leaves to challenge Polaris only to be casually flung away and saved by Dolphin. Meanwhile Tempest arrives to battle Polaris, freezing him only for him to free himself only for Aquaman to begin to assist Polaris's mental problem. However Dolphin then punches him before Aquaman can help Polaris, who then lifts the entire city emptying the water out through the front gates with the civilians except for Tempest and Aquaman, while Maxima arrives meeting with Dolphin.
name: Doctor in the House

description: The League confronts the evils of Darkseid! Black racer brings death to certain ones, once again! And in the past, Superman is ready to destroy the philosopher stone...an act that led to this future in the first place...
name: Rock of Ages, Part 5: Twilight of the Gods

description:
The world turns by infinite fractions, creating infinite possibilities for the future. Somewhere, a potential ally becomes a deadly enemy and a possible solution becomes an enigma. John Constantine knows that his past is inescapable. But now, someone else's past is catching up with him!

It's off to America when something seems to be making the Colonials quite mad.
name: Up The Down Staircase, Part 1
The Hellfire Hunt, Part 3: And He Shall Be Called... Man!
